ility with user devices or software</li> </ul> <p> In the event of a system-wide outage, the University will communicate instructions or deadline adjustments if appropriate. </p> <h2>9. Security Measures</h2> <p> The University uses a secure authentication system, encrypted password storage, and protected databases to safeguard user data. </p> <p>Users must follow all security requirements, including:</p> <ul> <li>Maintaining strong passwords</li> <li>Updating credentials when prompted</li> <li>Avoiding login from insecure or public devices</li> </ul> <p> Suspicious activity must be reported immediately. </p> <h2>10. Monitoring and Logging</h2> <p> To maintain system security, academic integrity, and compliance: </p> <ul> <li>User activity may be monitored</li> <li>Interactions may be logged</li> <li>File submissions, access history, and system usage may be recorded</li> </ul> <p> Monitoring is performed in accordance with University policy and applicable laws. </p> <h2>11. User-Submitted Content</h2> <p> Users are responsible for the accuracy, legality, and safety of any content they upload. </p> <p>The University is not liable for:</p> <ul> <li>Copyright violations caused by user uploads</li> <li>Harmful or inaccurate information uploaded by users</li> <li>User-generated content on discussion boards, submissions, or messaging areas</li> </ul> <p> The University may remove inappropriate or harmful content at its discretion. </p> <h2>12. Termination of Access</h2> <p> The University may suspend or terminate access to the Portal if: </p> <ul> <li>A user violates these Terms</li> <li>A user engages in harmful, disruptive, or unauthorised activities</li> <li>A user’s enrollment, employment, or affiliation with the University ends</li> </ul> <p> Termination may occur immediately if required for security purposes. </p> <h2>13. Limitation of Liability</h2> <p>The University of Studingham is not liable for:</p> <ul> <li>Technical issues beyond its control</li> <li>Loss of 