{
  "key": "privacy",
  "title": "Privacy Policy",
  "content": "<h2>1. Introduction</h2> <p> The University of Studingham (&#x22;the University&#x22;, &#x22;we&#x22;, &#x22;us&#x22;) is committed to protecting the privacy and security of all users who access the University Portal (&#x22;the Portal&#x22;). </p> <p> This Privacy Policy explains how personal data is collected, used, stored, and safeguarded. By accessing or using the Portal, users agree to the practices described in this policy. </p> <h2>2. Data Controller</h2> <p> The University of Studingham acts as the Data Controller, responsible for determining the purposes and methods of processing personal data through the Portal. </p> <p> Users may contact the University regarding privacy concerns through the official University email and communication channels provided in the Portal. </p> <h2>3. Purpose of the Portal</h2> <p>The Portal is designed to provide secure, reliable access to:</p> <ul> <li>Academic resources</li> <li>Learning materials</li> <li>Library facilities</li> <li>Timetables and course details</li> <li>File submissions and downloads</li> <li>University announcements and communication tools</li> <li>Administrative and academic management services</li> </ul> <h2>4. Types of Users</h2> <p>The Portal is used by:</p> <ul> <li>Students</li> <li>Tutors</li> <li>Administrative staff</li> </ul> <h2>5. Information We Collect</h2> <h3>5.1 Personal Identification Information</h3> <ul> <li>Full name</li> <li>University email address</li> <li>Student or Staff ID number</li> <li>Login credentials (encrypted passwords)</li> </ul> <h3>5.2 Academic and Activity Information</h3> <ul> <li>Course enrolments and lecture details</li> <li>Grades, transcripts, and assessment results</li> <li>Attendance records</li> <li>Timetables and meeting schedules</li> <li>Student finance details</li> <li>Library bookings</li> <li>File submissions, downloads, and course progress indicators</li> <li>Other educational interactions within the Portal</li> </ul> <h3>5.3 How Data Is Collected</h3> <p>Data is collected through:</p> <ul> <li>Registration forms completed during student enrolment or staff onboarding</li> <li>Automatic logging and system updates as users interact with Portal services</li> </ul> <h2>6. Purpose of Data Processing</h2> <p>We process personal data to:</p> <ul> <li>Authenticate and verify users</li> <li>Provide access to course materials and university services</li> <li>Ensure platform security and prevent unauthorised access</li> <li>Support teaching, learning, and academic administration</li> <li>Maintain accurate institutional and academic records</li> </ul> <h2>7. Legal Basis for Processing</h2> <h3>7.1 Contractual / Service Requirement</h3> <p>Processing is required to:</p> <ul> <li>Provide access to academic resources</li> <li>Display grades, progress indicators, and assignment submissions</li> <li>Facilitate communication between students, tutors, and staff</li> </ul> <h3>7.2 Legal Obligations</h3> <p> The University must maintain certain academic and administrative records in compliance with educational laws and regulatory requirements. </p> <h3>7.3 Public Task / Educational Mission</h3> <p> As part of its educational role, the University processes personal data to manage teaching, academic administration, and student services. </p> <h2>8. Data Sharing</h2> <p> The Portal does not share personal data with any external third parties. </p> <p> If future systems or integrations require data sharing, this section will be updated accordingly. </p> <h2>9. Security Measures</h2> <p>To protect all user data, the Portal uses:</p> <ul> <li>Encrypted passwords</li> <li>Secure authentication, including email-based verification during login</li> <li>Role-based access controls</li> <li>Encrypted data transfers</li> <li>Regular system monitoring and internal security audits</li> <li>Protection against unauthorised access, misuse, or modification</li> </ul> <p> The University prioritises technical and organisational security measures to safeguard all stored information. </p> <h2>10. Automated Decision-Making</h2> <p> The Portal does not use automated decision-making or profiling that impacts users. </p> <p>The only automated processing performed includes:</p> <ul> <li>Basic course progress calculations</li> <li>Completion percentages</li> <li>Class schedule organisation</li> </ul> <p> These functions do not produce decisions affecting user rights or access. </p> <h2>11. Children / Under-16 Use</h2> <p> The Portal is not intended for users under the age of 16. Only enrolled students, tutors, and administrative staff are permitted access. </p> <h2>12. Data Storage and Retention</h2> <h3>12.1 Storage</h3> <p> All personal data is stored securely within the University’s protected database systems. No data is transferred outside the University. </p> <h3>12.2 Retention</h3> <ul> <li>Students: Data is retained for the duration of their studies</li> <li>Staff: Data is retained for the duration of their employment or involvement</li> </ul> <p> After these periods, data is securely deleted or anonymised unless legal obligations require longer retention. </p> <h2>13. Data Breach Protocol</h2> <p>In the event of a data breach:</p> <ul> <li>The University will investigate immediately</li> <li>Affected users will be notified</li> <li>Authorities will be informed where legally required</li> </ul> <p> The University complies with applicable data protection regulations regarding breach response. </p> <h2>14. User Rights</h2> <p>All Portal users have the right to:</p> <ul> <li>Request access to their personal data</li> <li>Request correction of inaccurate or outdated information</li> <li>Request deletion of their data where legally permissible</li> <li>Object to improper handling of their information</li> <li>File a complaint with the University’s Data Protection contact</li> </ul> <h2>15. Cookies and Tracking</h2> <p> The Portal does not use cookies or tracking technologies. </p> <h2>16. Policy Updates</h2> <p> This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Users will be notified of any significant changes, and continued use of the Portal constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. </p> <h2>17. Contact Information</h2> <p> For privacy-related questions, data requests, or concerns, users may contact the University of Studingham through the official communication channels provided within the Portal. </p>"
